Installation:

    git clone git://github.com/abigagli/dotvim.git ~/.vim

Create symlinks:

    ln -s ~/.vim/vimrc ~/.vimrc
    ln -s ~/.vim/gvimrc ~/.gvimrc

Switch to the `~/.vim` directory, and fetch submodules:

    cd ~/.vim
    git submodule init
    git submodule update




To install plugins as git submodules:
NOTE:   To avoid pathogen#helptags() called by .vimrc dirtying the submodules's git repository tree,
        add an "ignore=dirty" line to the .gitmodules file for each submodule

    git submodule add http://github.com/vim-scripts/<plugin> bundle/<plugin>
    git add .
    git commit -m "Install <plugin> bundle as a submodule."

To upgrade a plugin bundle:

    cd ~/.vim/bundle/<plugin>
    git pull origin master

To upgrade ALL bundled plugins
    
    cd ~/.vim
    git submodule foreach git pull origin master

